# CoinWallet

Cross-platform wallet — Windows, Mac, iPhone, Android. **Bitcoin-first**; optional **Monero (XMR)** + user-initiated BTC↔XMR swap in Phase 10. Testnet first.

## Product Direction

- Native apps on all four platforms (Tauri desktop, Capacitor mobile)
- Public **download website** with Windows / Mac / iPhone / Android links
- **Leaderboard** — opt-in only; display name + total balance (no addresses or keys)
- **Advisor AI tab only** — on-device rule-based guidance (fees, privacy tips, explanations)
- **No trading AI** — no signals, automated market trading, or background swaps
- **Phase 10:** optional XMR wallets + manual BTC↔XMR swap (quote-and-confirm, privacy exit)
- Minimize cost: free Esplora APIs, no cloud LLM at launch

## Architecture

- `api/main.py` — FastAPI app, auth, status
- `api/wallet.py` — Wallet CRUD, sync, send
- `src/database.py` — Users, wallets, UTXOs, transactions, audit
- `src/wallet/` — Keys (BIP84), Esplora backend, wallet engine (embit)
- `admin/` — SvelteKit 5 + shadcn-svelte UI (shared across platforms)

See `.cursor/COINWALLET_MASTER_PLAN.md` for full roadmap and loop tasks.

## Safety Rules

- Default to **testnet** (`BITCOIN_NETWORK=testnet`)
- Never expose `encrypted_seed` or mnemonics in GET responses or audit logs
- Gate mainnet behind explicit configuration
- Never commit `.env`, `wallet.db`, or key material

## Development Guidelines

- Use Esplora for testnet chain data; Bitcoin Core RPC deferred to Phase 7
- Encrypt seeds at rest with `WALLET_ENCRYPTION_KEY`
- Audit sensitive actions (`WALLET_CREATED`, `TX_SENT`) without secrets
- Keep changes minimal and focused
- Mobile/desktop packaging should reuse `admin/` UI — avoid platform-specific forks
